    <text>
        <body>
            <head>182. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                    (<persName corresp="rectQC2yY4UhXLeKu">Brzezinski</persName>) to Secretary of
                State <persName corresp="recRM4qiy2MVhNDPu">Vance</persName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d182fn1">Source: Carter Library,
                    National Security Affairs, Brzezinski Material, Country File, Box 56, Morocco:
                    9/79–1/81. Confidential. A copy was sent to <persName
                        corresp="reco12xHs2VU4n3PC">Brown</persName>.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1980-01-22"
                        >January 22, 1980</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <list type="subject">
                <head>SUBJECT</head>
                <item>
                    <placeName corresp="recLpHNCu4qy8XTDl">Morocco</placeName>
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recYitJjr1dXM44FB">Arms Sales</rs> Package (U)</item>
            </list>
            <p>To confirm the understanding we reached earlier today, the arms package being readied
                for formal <orgName corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">Congressional</orgName> notification
                this week should include 20 <rs type="topic" corresp="rec3QSbxhrMctVdHq">F–5
                    aircraft</rs>. It is understood that provision of all 20 aircraft to <placeName
                    corresp="recLpHNCu4qy8XTDl">Morocco</placeName> is conditional upon Moroccan
                progress toward a political negotiation of the <placeName
                    corresp="recGZlEaPYk6Kf3qK">Western Sahara</placeName> conflict and that we will
                retain strict control over the pace of delivery; that point should be stressed in
                our presentation to <orgName corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">Congress</orgName>. (C)</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>
                    <persName corresp="rectQC2yY4UhXLeKu">
                        <hi rendition="simple_bold">Zbigniew Brzezinski</hi>
                    </persName>
                </signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
